  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis damage accumulation model employs the power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger correlation, whose theoretical derivation assumes a linear superposition of stress-exposure history (i.e., path-independent, linear damage accumulation). This linearity precondition is satisfied in the single-pass laminar-dominated validation dataset used to calibrate model constants; however, the CPB COU involves recirculating turbulent flow fields across five flow-speed combinations spanning 2.0–6.0 L/min at 2500–4500 RPM, where nonlinear stress-history interactions may arise and the linearity assumption has not been independently verified for this operating envelope.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-rh-criterion",
