      "rationale": "Velocity magnitude and wall shear stress fields feed directly into the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law to compute NIH, which maps to RH via predicate device normalization. The QoIs are therefore directly relevant to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1). Relevance requirement at MRL 2 is satisfied."
