    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid properties, and operating regime are sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating envelope to support credibility at MRL 2. Differences are documented and judged acceptable.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same geometry as the COU device. Bovine blood analog fluid properties are consistent with clinical blood viscosity ranges. The validation operating point (4.0 L/min, 3500 RPM) lies within the COU envelope (2.0–6.0 L/min, 2500–4500 RPM). Relevance of validation activities to the COU is judged sufficient for MRL 2. Note: the power-law damage accumulation model assumes linear superposition of stress-exposure history; this assumption was implicitly satisfied at the single laminar validation point but has not been verified across the broader recirculating turbulent COU operating range. The acceptance criteria for this factor do not address verification of the linearity precondition."
    },
