      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) justified for rotating internal flow; hemolysis damage model form documented with theoretical basis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on literature evidence for rotating pump flows. Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model adopted per FDA guidance and published benchmark studies. Model form is documented and justified. The power-law model is theoretically valid under the assumption of linear, path-independent damage accumulation — a precondition that holds for the laminar single-pass regime in which the model was originally derived and validated here, and which is assumed to extend to the full COU operating envelope without explicit verification."
